{"id":"1902.05012","submitter":"Joseph Tindall","authors":"Joseph Tindall, Berislav Buca, Jonathan R. Coulthard, Dieter Jaksch","title":"Heating-Induced Long-Range $\\eta$-Pairing in the Hubbard Model","comments":"Main Text: 6 Pages, 3 Figures. Supplemental Material: 4 Pages, 3\n  Figures","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. Lett. 123, 030603 (2019)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevLett.123.030603","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph cond-mat.str-el cond-mat.supr-con","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We show how, upon heating the spin degrees of freedom of the Hubbard model to\ninfinite temperature, the symmetries of the system allow the creation of\nsteady-states with long-range correlations between $\\eta$-pairs. With induce\nthis heating with either dissipation or periodic driving and evolve the system\ntowards a nonequilibrium steady state, a process which melts all spin order in\nthe system. The steady state is identical in both cases and displays\ndistance-invariant off-diagonal $\\eta$-correlations. These correlations were\nfirst recognised in the superconducting eigenstates in Yang's seminal paper\n[Phys. Rev. Lett 63, 2144 (1989)], which are a subset of our steady states. We\nshow that our results are a consequence of symmetry properties and entirely\nindependent of the microscopic details of the model and the heating mechanism.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Feb 2019 17:10:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 19 Jul 2019 11:01:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-22"}
