ar wind velocities are insufficient for internal, X-ray\nemitting shocks to form. Our results are consistent with recent findings that\nmassive binaries are not uniformly brighter than single stars of comparable\nluminosity and spectral type, although it is noteworthy that the brightest and\nhardest stellar X-ray sources within Wd1 are all either confirmed or candidate\nmassive, interacting/post-interaction binaries (Abridged).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 14 Feb 2019 12:22:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-06-19"}
