of condensed carbon varies between 5%\nand 40%, and the gas-to-dust ratios between 500 and 10000. Furthermore, stellar\nevolution models can use the mass-loss rates calculated from DARWIN models at\nsolar metallicity when modeling the AGB phase at subsolar metallicities if\ncarbon excess is used as the critical abundance parameter instead of the C/O\nratio.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 14 Feb 2019 13:46:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-03-20"}
